The paper deals with algorithmic and complexity aspects of a graph class called H-graphs, which are intersection graphs of connected subgraphs of some subdivision of a fixed graph H. This makes the paper relevant to several subfields of computer science. 

cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is the most likely category as the paper deals with graph theory and combinatorial optimization problems. 

cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper discusses algorithmic aspects of H-graphs. 

cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is relevant as the paper provides complexity analysis of several optimization problems on H-graphs. 

cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is relevant as the paper deals with intersection graphs of subgraphs of a fixed graph. 

cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) is relevant as the paper discusses the complexity of finding maximum cliques in H-graphs, which is a fundamental problem in game theory.
